# http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#RiskClass> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Devices with the highest risk profile, which are vital for supporting life, have direct contact with the heart/central circulatory system, or are permanently implanted, such as cardiac pacemakers, heart valves, and breast implants."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class III"@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#RiskClass> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Devices with a moderate risk level, often used for short-term, non-critical, or diagnostic purposes, such as hearing aids, ultrasound equipment, or standard catheters."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIa> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class IIa"@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#RiskClass> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Devices that pose significant risk, often including active devices meant for monitoring or administering substances, or long-term implants, such as ventilators, infusion pumps, or bone fixation devices."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ClassIIb> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class IIb"@en .
