<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#ActionType> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#UserNotice> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It is a mandatory communication sent by a medical device manufacturer to users (hospitals, doctors, patients) to prevent or reduce the risk of a serious incident with a device that is already on the market" .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Safety alert"@en .
# 
