<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SelfTest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It is an in vitro diagnostic medical device intended by the manufacturer for use by laypersons in a home environment."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SelfTest> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Self test"@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#Serious
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#Serious> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#Serious> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#IncidentType> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#Serious> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It is defined as any incident involving a device that directly or indirectly led, might have led, or might lead to the death of a patient/user, a serious deterioration in health (temporary/permanent), or a serious public health threat. It includes malfunctions, performance issues, and use errors."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#Serious> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Serious"@en .
# 
# http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SingleUse
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SingleUse> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SingleUse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#DeviceType> .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SingleUse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "It is defined as a device intended to be used on one individual patient during a single procedure and then discarded. They are not intended to be reprocessed or reused."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/bea/ontologies/2026/3clasificacion_MDR_IVDR#SingleUse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Single use"@en .
# 
